org.fxmisc.wellbehaved.event

Enum InputHandler.Result

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<InputHandler.Result>
      • org.fxmisc.wellbehaved.event.InputHandler.Result
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<InputHandler.Result>
    Enclosing interface:
    InputHandler<T extends javafx.event.Event>

    public static enum InputHandler.Result
extends java.lang.Enum<InputHandler.Result>
    Signifies what to do after handling some input:
    • continue trying to match the event type with the next given EventPattern (PROCEED)
    • stop trying to match the event type and consume the event (CONSUME)
    • stop trying to match the event type and do not consume it (IGNORE)

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      CONSUME
      Stop trying to match the event type with the next given EventPattern and consume the event
      IGNORE
      Stop trying to match the event type with the next given EventPattern and do not consume it
      PROCEED
      Try to continue to match the event type with the next given EventPattern.

      • PROCEED

        public static final InputHandler.Result PROCEED
        Try to continue to match the event type with the next given EventPattern. This can be used to run some code before an InputHandler that consumes the event.

        Stop trying to match the event type with the next given EventPattern and consume the event

      • IGNORE
